</taxonomicName>
is always confused with its close congener 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6251B10FC52FF9BFAA4FF09" authority="(Herbst, 1803)" baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[1017,1313,188,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philyra">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FC52FF9BFB95FF09" box="[1017,1040,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FB8BFF9AFBF4FF09" box="[1056,1137,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
(Herbst, 1803)
</taxonomicName>
. The latter has been frequently recorded from the Persian Gulf [
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6251B10FD42FFF9FC17FF2A" author="Nobili, G." box="[745,914,223,247]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="13 - 159" refId="ref51383" refString="Nobili, G. (1906 a) Crustaces decapodes et stomatopodes. In: Mission J. Bonnier et Ch. Perez (Golfe Persique, 1901). Bulletin Scientifique de la France et de la Belgique, 40, 13 - 159, pls. 2 - 7." type="journal article" year="1906">Nobili (1906a)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6251B10FC12FFC7FB72FF2A" authorityName="Kossmann" authorityYear="1877" box="[953,1271,224,248]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="philyra" variety="mascarenica">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FC12FFC7FC55FF25" box="[953,976,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FC74FFC6FBB5FF25" box="[991,1072,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FBC2FFC6FB72FF2A" box="[1129,1271,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">mascarenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Arzanah I.; 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6251B10FF13FE22FE0EFEC1" author="Stephensen, K." box="[184,395,260,284]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="57 - 237" refId="ref52943" refString="Stephensen, K. (1946) The Brachyura of the Iranian Gulf. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part IV. E. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 57 - 237." type="book chapter" year="1946">Stephensen (1946)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6251B10FE1EFE23FD72FEC1" authorityName="Kossmann" authorityYear="1877" box="[437,759,260,284]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="philyra" variety="mascarenica">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FE1EFE23FE49FEC1" box="[437,460,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FE77FE22FDA8FEC1" box="[476,557,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FDC2FE23FD72FEC1" box="[617,759,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">mascarenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C6251B10FCEBFE22FC19FEC1" box="[832,924,260,284]" name="Bahrain" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Bahrain</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6251B10FC01FE22FB00FEC1" author="Evans, G. &amp; Murray, J. W. &amp; Biggs, H. E. J. &amp; Bate, R. &amp; Bush P. R." box="[938,1157,260,284]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="233 - 277" refId="ref46962" refString="Evans, G., Murray, J. W., Biggs, H. E. J., Bate, R. &amp; Bush P. R. (1973) The oceanography, ecology, sedimentology and geomorphology of parts of the Trucial Coast Barrier Island Complex, Persian Gulf. In: Purser, B. H. (ed.): The Persian Gulf. - Holocene carbonate sedimentation and diagenesis in a shallow epicontinental sea. Springer Verlag, Berlin, 233 - 277." type="book chapter" year="1973">
Evans 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FC5CFE23FBACFEC1" box="[1015,1065,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (1973)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6251B10FB6BFE22FAD9FEC1" author="Titgen, R. H." box="[1216,1372,260,284]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref53402" refString="Titgen, R. H. (1982) The systematics and ecology of the Decapods of Dubai, and their zoogeographic relationships to the Persian Gulf and the Western Indian Ocean. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Texas A &amp; M University, 292 pp." type="book" year="1982">Titgen (1982)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C6251B10FF3CFE01FF51FEE2" box="[151,212,295,319]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">UAE</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6251B10FF4BFE0EFE46FEE2" author="Basson, P. W. &amp; Burchard, J. E. &amp; Hardy, J. T. &amp; Price, A. R. G." box="[224,451,295,320]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref45702" refString="Basson, P. W., Burchard, J. E., Hardy, J. T. &amp; Price, A. R. G. (1977) Biotopes of the Western Arabian Gulf: Marine life and environments of Saudi Arabia. ARAMCO, Dept. of Loss Prevention and environmental affairs, Dhahran: 289 pp." type="book" year="1977">
Basson 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FE93FE0FFEEFFE9D" box="[312,362,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (1977)
</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C6251B10FDA2FE01FD24FEE2" box="[521,673,295,319]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6251B10FD07FE01FCB0FEE2" author="Apel, M." box="[684,821,295,319]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel (2001)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C6251B10FCD0FE01FB8BFEE2" box="[891,1038,295,319]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C6251B10FBEDFE01FB03FEE2" box="[1094,1158,295,319]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">UAE</collectingCountry>
]. 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6251B10FB33FE01FAA4FEE2" author="Apel, M." box="[1176,1313,295,319]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel (2001)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the Persian Gulf records all could be clearly assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6251B10FCA0FE6BFC04FEB9" baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[779,897,332,356]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philyra">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FCA0FE6BFCA7FEB9" box="[779,802,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FC9BFE6AFC04FEB9" box="[816,897,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Buitendijk (1939) prepared detailed remarks in order to distinguish these two similar species, and provided synonymies for both species using literature records. By using Buitendijk (1939) and the key provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6251B10FCACFEB2FBA3FE71" author="Griffin, D. J. G. &amp; Tranter, H. A." box="[775,1062,404,428]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 335" refId="ref47564" refString="Griffin, D. J. G. &amp; Tranter, H. A. (1986) The Decapoda Brachyura of the Siboga Expedition. Part VIII. Majidae. Siboga Expeditie Monographie, 39 c 4, 1 - 335." type="journal article" year="1986">Griffin &amp; Tranter (1986)</bibRefCitation>
the present specimens from the Iranian coast of the Persian Gulf could be convincingly identified as 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6251B10FC34FE9FFB98FE0D" baseAuthorityName="Ruppel" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[927,1053,440,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platipes">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FC34FE9FFC33FE0D" box="[927,950,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FC6FFE9EFB98FE0D" box="[964,1053,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">platipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We could not examine the single male of 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6251B10FF59FEFAFE46FE29" author="Stephensen, K." box="[242,451,476,500]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="57 - 237" refId="ref52943" refString="Stephensen, K. (1946) The Brachyura of the Iranian Gulf. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part IV. E. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 57 - 237." type="book chapter" year="1946">Stephensen (1946)</bibRefCitation>
collected by Danish Expedition from 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C6251B10FCC5FEFAFC4CFE29" box="[878,969,476,500]" name="Bahrain" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Bahrain</collectingCountry>
, but the drawing of the male G1 provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6251B10FF12FED9FE3FFDCA" author="Stephensen, K." box="[185,442,511,535]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="57 - 237" refId="ref52943" refString="Stephensen, K. (1946) The Brachyura of the Iranian Gulf. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part IV. E. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 57 - 237." type="book chapter" year="1946">Stephensen (1946: 109</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 21e–f) is very similar to the figure of the G1 provided by Buitendijk (1939: 253, fig. 22) for 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6251B10FF53FD03FEF8FDE1" baseAuthorityName="Ruppel" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[248,381,548,572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platipes">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FF53FD03FE8AFDE1" box="[248,271,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FE8FFD02FEF8FDE1" box="[292,381,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">platipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than that of 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6251B10FDD9FD03FD6AFDE1" baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[626,751,548,572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philyra">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FDD9FD03FD0CFDE1" box="[626,649,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FD35FD02FD6AFDE1" box="[670,751,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although, 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6251B10FC29FD02FB95FDE1" author="Apel, M." box="[898,1040,548,572]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel (2001)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the Persian Gulf specimens, which are all recorded from the Arabian coast, are 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6251B10FCF7FD6FFC56FDBD" baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1803" box="[860,979,584,608]" class="Malacostraca" family="Majidae" genus="Micippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philyra">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FCF7FD6FFCF6FDBD" box="[860,883,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6251B10FC29FD6EFC56FDBD" box="[898,979,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">philyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We think that still all the material must be re-examined in order to clarify the occurrence of these two species in the Persian Gulf.
</paragraph>
